WEBVTT

00:00.773 --> 00:04.232
<i>- Previously on The Resident...
- I loved my sister very much.</i>

00:04.242 --> 00:07.303
One night, I decided to take
a quick nap, and when I woke up,

00:07.313 --> 00:09.071
the whole house was on fire.

00:09.081 --> 00:11.473
- CONRAD: How's Jessie?
- Her kidneys are failing.

00:11.483 --> 00:13.469
I was a project for you,
and now it's finished.

00:13.480 --> 00:16.415
Tell me I'm wrong. Tell me I'm right.
Either way, just open up

00:16.426 --> 00:18.381
- like you asked me to do.
- And I will.

00:18.391 --> 00:20.386
When I'm ready,
when I figure some things out.

00:20.397 --> 00:22.283
I mean, my feelings
aren't just gonna change.

00:22.294 --> 00:24.678
Conrad and I have fought long
and hard for our relationship.

00:24.689 --> 00:25.947
We've been through it.

00:25.958 --> 00:27.193
But I love him.

00:27.666 --> 00:28.924
(LAUGHTER)

00:28.934 --> 00:30.393
<i>♪ Get up offa that thing... ♪</i>

00:30.403 --> 00:32.159
Come on!

00:32.170 --> 00:34.029
<i>♪ Get up offa that thing ♪</i>

00:34.039 --> 00:36.431
<i>♪ And dance till you, sing it now ♪</i>

00:36.441 --> 00:39.001
<i>- (SHOUTING, LAUGHING)
- ♪ Get up offa that thing ♪</i>

00:39.011 --> 00:40.436
<i>♪ And dance till you feel better ♪</i>

00:40.446 --> 00:42.671
<i>♪ Get up offa that thing ♪</i>

00:42.681 --> 00:44.339
<i>♪ And try to release that pressure ♪</i>

00:44.349 --> 00:45.842
<i>♪ Get up offa that thing... ♪</i>

00:45.852 --> 00:47.710
It's freezing.

00:47.720 --> 00:50.079
They're expecting six more inches.

00:50.089 --> 00:52.448
Atlanta is essentially shut down.

00:52.458 --> 00:53.749
So is the hospital.

00:53.759 --> 00:55.684
Bell canceled elective procedures.

00:55.694 --> 00:58.588
<i>♪ Get up offa that thing ♪</i>

00:58.598 --> 01:01.089
<i>♪ And try to release that pressure ♪</i>

01:01.099 --> 01:02.558
<i>♪ Get up off... ♪</i>

01:02.568 --> 01:04.693
The med students need to go home.

01:04.703 --> 01:06.796
They make good snowball targets,
but otherwise,

01:06.806 --> 01:08.430
they're useless. They need to go.

01:08.440 --> 01:10.299
I don't know. A slow night

01:10.309 --> 01:12.368
is a good time for them
to practice their skills.

01:12.378 --> 01:14.313
(LAUGHTER)

01:16.347 --> 01:19.121
You keep these children,
they're your responsibility.

01:19.132 --> 01:20.710
<i>♪ And try to release that pressure ♪</i>

01:20.720 --> 01:22.912
<i>♪ Get up offa that thing ♪</i>

01:22.922 --> 01:24.579
<i>♪ And twist till you feel better ♪</i>

01:24.589 --> 01:27.582
<i>♪ Get up offa that thing ♪</i>

01:27.592 --> 01:29.217
<i>♪ And shake it, sing it now ♪</i>

01:29.227 --> 01:31.254
<i>♪ Get up offa that thing... ♪</i>

01:31.920 --> 01:33.777
Look at you.

01:33.788 --> 01:35.768
The most popular girl on dialysis.

01:35.779 --> 01:37.605
JESSIE: Yeah, apparently kidney failure

01:37.616 --> 01:39.404
comes with more visitors than rehab.

01:39.415 --> 01:41.696
- CONRAD: How are you holding up?
- I don't feel great.

01:42.175 --> 01:43.599
It's hard to keep my eyes open.

01:43.609 --> 01:45.635
It's really taking a toll on her.

01:45.645 --> 01:48.772
Dr. Shaw says that some people
have to do this three days a week,

01:48.782 --> 01:50.624
- four hours a session?
- Now, there's no need

01:50.635 --> 01:52.497
to get ahead of ourselves.
We're doing a workup

01:52.508 --> 01:54.189
to see if your
kidney failure's reversible.

01:54.200 --> 01:55.621
We'll have a better idea real soon.

01:55.632 --> 01:57.914
I didn't know you added another
doctor to your dance card.

01:57.925 --> 01:59.883
Well, yeah, the clinic's closed
because of the storm.

01:59.893 --> 02:02.476
I came by to help out and figure I'd
drop in and meet Nic's sister, too.

02:02.487 --> 02:03.548
Can I steal you?

02:03.559 --> 02:06.079
- Donna's asking for us.
- Oh, this is important.

02:06.090 --> 02:07.765
It's a patient we've had a long time.

02:07.776 --> 02:09.201
- JESSIE: You'll be back soon?
- Yes.

02:09.211 --> 02:10.704
JESSIE: Okay.

02:10.715 --> 02:12.706
<i>CONRAD: Alec is into you.</i>

02:12.717 --> 02:15.660
- I noticed.
- So I'm right.

02:16.082 --> 02:18.867
He mentioned something,
but I shut it down.

02:18.877 --> 02:20.808
Must be complicated
to have to work with him.

02:20.819 --> 02:23.441
- NIC: I'm fine.
- I'm sure you are.

02:24.426 --> 02:25.818
Can I punch him?

02:26.852 --> 02:27.880
Kidding.

02:27.891 --> 02:30.855
- This is the new Conrad, remember?
- (NIC CHUCKLES)

02:30.866 --> 02:32.725
- Thanks.
- Thank you.

02:32.736 --> 02:34.220
Look, I'm handling it.

02:34.231 --> 02:35.888
- Trust me.
- Of course I trust you.

02:35.899 --> 02:37.829
I don't have to be friends
with the guy, though.

02:37.839 --> 02:39.298
No, you don't.

02:39.308 --> 02:40.532
Hey, Donna.

02:40.543 --> 02:42.997
- How you feeling?
- Not bad.

02:43.008 --> 02:45.779
Ready to talk about how I'm gonna die?

02:46.982 --> 02:48.973
(NIC SIGHS)

02:48.983 --> 02:50.955
There. You'll be fine.

02:50.966 --> 02:53.845
You probably shouldn't try to get home
until the snowplows come through.

02:53.856 --> 02:55.891
Nurse Hundley will find you a cozy spot.

02:58.160 --> 02:59.817
What's going on?

02:59.827 --> 03:01.887
Hmm? Oh, Bell's making an announcement.

03:01.897 --> 03:04.690
So, as you know, the blizzard
is getting worse by the hour.

03:04.700 --> 03:06.824
We're already working
with a skeleton staff,

03:06.834 --> 03:08.845
and because conditions are so hazardous,

03:08.856 --> 03:11.389
we expect the next shift is
gonna have trouble getting here,

03:11.400 --> 03:14.059
so no matter what your specialty,

03:14.442 --> 03:16.435
just help where you're needed.

03:16.445 --> 03:18.569
I mean, so far we've been lucky,
it's been quiet,

03:18.579 --> 03:22.118
- but we can expect storm-related...
- (HORN HONKING)

03:24.889 --> 03:27.092
complications all night.

03:27.956 --> 03:30.893
(HORN CONTINUES HONKING)

03:32.393 --> 03:36.099
- (EMTS SHOUTING)
- (TIRES SCREECHING)

03:39.567 --> 03:41.469
(GROANING)

03:43.638 --> 03:45.130
- IRVING: Where does it hurt?
- EMT: Right here.

03:45.140 --> 03:46.632
Are you guys okay?

03:46.642 --> 03:48.466
Look, we're fine,
but my dad, he needs help.

03:48.476 --> 03:51.079
He's in the back. He's frozen.
We dug him out of the snow.

